V<p><a href="http://cdn.linuxaria.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/cover.png" rel="lightbox[7057]"><img alt="Monstrerpg2" class="alignright  wp-image-7059" height="359" src="http://cdn.linuxaria.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/03/cover.png" width="251" /></a></p>\u000a<p>Disclaimer: If you like fast paced action games, or games with a stunning graphics, move away.<br />\u000aMonster RPG 2 is a free/open source console style role playing game (perhaps most accurately, a JRPG) with a lot of depth and old-school character. It is available for iDevices (iPhone, iPod Touch, iPad), Android, PC (Windows, Mac, Linux) and now Raspberry Pi.</p>\u000a<p>Some of its main features are:</p>\u000a<ul>\u000a<li>Nineteen locations to discover and explore</li>\u000a<li>Nine adventurers to add to the party, develop and lead.</li>\u000a<li>Turn-based combat against over ninety monster types.</li>\u000a<li>Eighteen spells for Magic Users and Clerics to cast (not including spells cast by monsters!)</li>\u000a<li>Enough swords, guns, potions, helmets, badges, keys, staves and armor to keep any adventurer stocked for life.</li>\u000a</ul>\u000a<p>The game has been <a href="http://www.indiegogo.com/projects/monster-rpg-2-open-jrpg-game-engine?website_name=monster-rpg-2-open-jrpg-game-engine" target="_blank">&#8220;liberated&#8221; in November 2012</a>, when the author raised 1500$ to release the code and distribute freely the game for all the platforms.</p>\u000a<p><span id="more-7057"></span><br />\u000a<!--\u000agoogle_ad_client = "ca-pub-2431705124166952";\u000a/* Leader-text-image */\u000agoogle_ad_slot = "4350381014";\u000agoogle_ad_width = 728;\u000agoogle_ad_height = 90;\u000a//--><br />\u000a<br />\u000aMonster RPG 2 is a classic game of search with a fantasy background that makes you discover the continents and worlds created for this game and lets you take a simple character with no special skills and develop it into a hero with the power to save his world.</p>\u000a<p>Monster RPG 2 is a turn-based role-playing game with enough variety, plot twists, secrets, and scenery that will make you go back to replay it several times even after a long time. If you loved the classic 16-bit games on older consoles such the SNES, you&#8217;ll love this game.</p>\u000a<p>The graphics are definitely old-fashioned, as you can see from the video, but the story is good and also the character development is quite interesting, so I think that it might be a nice alternative to spend a few hours of fun in the old way.</p>\u000a\u000a<p><strong>Installation</strong></p>\u000a<p>It&#8217;s possible to <a href="http://www.monster-rpg.com/download.html" target="_blank">download the game directly from the official website</a> as linux binary for 32 and 64 bit architecture, or you can download it via <a href="http://www.desura.com/games/monster-rpg-2" target="_blank">Desura</a></p>\u000a<h3>Conclusions</h3>\u000a<p>Graphics: The sprites are nice and remind the first Final Fantasy games such as FF4 or FF5. The battle backgrounds blend well with the battle sprites and is well done.<br />\u000aSound: The sound and music are a key of any RPG to set the proper mood or introduce a new scenario, the team made a good work on this side.<br />\u000aGamplay:  The gameplay is what you could expect from this game, the development of the characters is one of the things you&#8217;ll probably like, as you can choose how to growth your characters.</p>\u000a<p>Overall: If you have seen the video and you have thought &#8220;this game could be nice&#8221; than probably you&#8217;ll love this small game, as wrote above stay away if you search for stunning graphics.<br />\u000a<!--\u000agoogle_ad_client = "ca-pub-2431705124166952";\u000a/* Leader-text-image */\u000agoogle_ad_slot = "4350381014";\u000agoogle_ad_width = 728;\u000agoogle_ad_height = 90;\u000a//--><br />\u000a</p>\u000a<div class="yarpp-related-rss">\u000a<p>Related posts:<ol>\u000a<li><a href="http://linuxaria.com/recensioni/4-proprietary-game-from-ubuntu-software-center?lang=en" rel="bookmark" title="4 Proprietary game from Ubuntu software center">4 Proprietary game from Ubuntu software center</a></li>\u000a<li><a href="http://linuxaria.com/article/5-new-rpg-games-for-linux?lang=en" rel="bookmark" title="5 New RPG games for Linux">5 New RPG games for Linux</a></li>\u000a</ol></p>\u000a<img src="http://yarpp.org/pixels/ba2be3fba9b21a2a23229e17892b86c0" />\u000a</div>\u000a <p><a href="http://linuxaria.com/?flattrss_redirect&amp;id=7057&amp;md5=4ad174a1ca2878f6cd3e50760b978973" target="_blank" title="Flattr"><img alt="flattr this!" src="http://cdn.linuxaria.com/wp-content/plugins/flattr/img/flattr-badge-large.png" /></a></p><div class="feedflare">\u000a<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?a=_Rj8WkSlPrw:HP6KY56OIAY:yIl2AUoC8zA"><img border="0" src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?d=yIl2AUoC8zA" /></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?a=_Rj8WkSlPrw:HP6KY56OIAY:qj6IDK7rITs"><img border="0" src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?d=qj6IDK7rITs" /></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?a=_Rj8WkSlPrw:HP6KY56OIAY:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img border="0" src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Linuxaria_En?i=_Rj8WkSlPrw:HP6KY56OIAY:gIN9vFwOqvQ" /></a>\u000a</div><img height="1" src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Linuxaria_En/~4/_Rj8WkSlPrw" width="1" />
