VSteganography is the art and science of writing hidden messages in such a way that no one, apart from the sender and intended recipient, suspects the existence of the message, a form of security through obscurity. The word steganography is of Greek origin and means &#8220;concealed writing&#8221; from the Greek words steganos (\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03b3\u03b1\u03bd\u03cc\u03c2) meaning &#8220;covered <a class="excerpt-more" href="http://linuxaria.com/article/steganography-or-how-to-hide-text-in-image-or-sound-file?lang=en">[...]</a><div class="yarpp-related-rss">\u000a\u000aRelated posts:<ol>\u000a<li><a href="http://linuxaria.com/article/secure-deletion-of-data-in-linux?lang=en" rel="bookmark" title="Secure Deletion of Data in Linux">Secure Deletion of Data in Linux</a></li>\u000a<li><a href="http://linuxaria.com/article/introduction-to-the-gimp-gnu-image-manipulation-program?lang=en" rel="bookmark" title="Introduction to The GIMP (GNU Image Manipulation Program)">Introduction to The GIMP (GNU Image Manipulation Program)</a></li>\u000a</ol>\u000a<img src="http://yarpp.org/pixels/ba2be3fba9b21a2a23229e17892b86c0" />\u000a</div>
